   <h1><b>What is HTML?</b></h1>
   <p>HTML is the standard markup language for creating websites<br>
    and is usually used in tandem with other languages used for <br>
    styling the website.</p>
    <h1><b>HTML requirements:</b></h1>
    <p>To tell your computer that you are using HTML to code the<br>
     the website, you must use these elements: &#60;DOCTYPE html&#62;,<br>
    &#60;HTML&#62; and &#60;/HTML&#62;, and &#60;head&#62;. &#60;DOCTYPE html&#62;<br>
     shows that the document will be using HTML. The space in between<br>
     the &#60;HTML&#62; and &#60;/HTML&#62; is where you write your<br>
     HTML code and will tell the computer where the HTML is on the screen.<br>
    &#60;head&#62; allows you to put in the meta information about how the <br>
     website will be organizedm it is extremely important for making the website<br>
      accessable.</p>
     <h1><b>Writing Elements</b></h1>
     <p>In order to put writing on your website you must use these<br>
      elements: &#60;title&#62;, &#60;body&#62;, &#60;p&#62;, and<br>
      &#60;br&#62;.
       &#60;title:&#62; puts in a title, &#60;body&#62; allows you to put paragraphs<br>
      and writing inside of it, &#60;p&#62; allows you to write, and &#60;br&#62;<br>
      allows you to put paragraph breaks.</p>
      <h1><b>Writing Formatting:</b></h1>
      <p>To organize your writing and format it properly, you can use these elements:<br>
       &#60;hr&#62;, &#60;!-- --&#62;, and &#60;div&#62;. &#60;hr&#62; allows you to<br>
        put in lines in between paragraphs, &#60;!-- --&#62; allows you to add comments,<br>
        and &#60;div&#62; allows you to put in larger paragraph breaks.</p>
        <h1><b>Other Elements</b></h1>
        <p> Some other elements that are just as useful in creating your website are:<br>
        &#60;a&#62; &#60;img&#62; &#60;ul&#62; &#60;ol&#62; &#60;li&#62; &#60;table&#62;<br>
        &#60;tr&#62; &#60;th&#62; &#60;td&#62;. &#60;a&#62; allows you to put in links<br>
        &#60;img&#62; allows you to add images, &#60;ul&#62; &#60;ol&#62; &#60;li&#62;<br>
        are all for creating different types of lists, and &#60;tr&#62; &#60;th&#62; &#60;td&#62;<br> are all for making different types of tables.</p>
        <h1><b>HTML elements</b></h1>
